33template <class T>
34RTCError VerifyCodecPreferences(const std::vector<RtpCodecCapability>& codecs,
35 const std::vector<T>& send_codecs,
36 const std::vector<T>& recv_codecs) {
37 // If the intersection between codecs and
38 // RTCRtpSender.getCapabilities(kind).codecs or the intersection between
39 // codecs and RTCRtpReceiver.getCapabilities(kind).codecs only contains RTX,
40 // RED or FEC codecs or is an empty set, throw InvalidModificationError.
41 // This ensures that we always have something to offer, regardless of
42 // transceiver.direction.
43
44 if (!absl::c_any_of(codecs, [&recv_codecs](const RtpCodecCapability& codec) {
45 return codec.name != cricket::kRtxCodecName &&
46 codec.name != cricket::kRedCodecName &&
47 codec.name != cricket::kFlexfecCodecName &&
48 absl::c_any_of(recv_codecs, [&codec](const T& recv_codec) {
49 return recv_codec.MatchesCapability(codec);
50 });
51 })) {
52 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_MODIFICATION,
53 "Invalid codec preferences: Missing codec from recv "
54 "codec capabilities.");
55 }
56
57 if (!absl::c_any_of(codecs, [&send_codecs](const RtpCodecCapability& codec) {
58 return codec.name != cricket::kRtxCodecName &&
59 codec.name != cricket::kRedCodecName &&
60 codec.name != cricket::kFlexfecCodecName &&
61 absl::c_any_of(send_codecs, [&codec](const T& send_codec) {
62 return send_codec.MatchesCapability(codec);
63 });
64 })) {
65 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_MODIFICATION,
66 "Invalid codec preferences: Missing codec from send "
67 "codec capabilities.");
68 }
69
70 // Let codecCapabilities be the union of
71 // RTCRtpSender.getCapabilities(kind).codecs and
72 // RTCRtpReceiver.getCapabilities(kind).codecs. For each codec in codecs, If
73 // codec is not in codecCapabilities, throw InvalidModificationError.
74 for (const auto& codec_preference : codecs) {
75 bool is_recv_codec =
76 absl::c_any_of(recv_codecs, [&codec_preference](const T& codec) {
77 return codec.MatchesCapability(codec_preference);
78 });
79
80 bool is_send_codec =
81 absl::c_any_of(send_codecs, [&codec_preference](const T& codec) {
82 return codec.MatchesCapability(codec_preference);
83 });
84
85 if (!is_recv_codec && !is_send_codec) {
86 return RTCError(
87 RTCErrorType::INVALID_MODIFICATION,
88 std::string("Invalid codec preferences: invalid codec with name \"") +
89 codec_preference.name + "\".");
90 }
91 }
92
93 // Check we have a real codec (not just rtx, red or fec)
94 if (absl::c_all_of(codecs, [](const RtpCodecCapability& codec) {
95 return codec.name == cricket::kRtxCodecName ||
96 codec.name == cricket::kRedCodecName ||
97 codec.name == cricket::kUlpfecCodecName;
98 })) {
99 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_MODIFICATION,
100 "Invalid codec preferences: codec list must have a non "
101 "RTX, RED or FEC entry.");
102 }
103
104 return RTCError::OK();
105}

107TaskQueueBase* GetCurrentTaskQueueOrThread() {
108 TaskQueueBase* current = TaskQueueBase::Current();
109 if (!current)
110 current = rtc::ThreadManager::Instance()->CurrentThread();
111 return current;
112}

116RtpTransceiver::RtpTransceiver(
117 cricket::MediaType media_type,
118 cricket::ChannelManager* channel_manager /* = nullptr*/)
119 : thread_(GetCurrentTaskQueueOrThread()),
120 unified_plan_(false),
121 media_type_(media_type),
122 channel_manager_(channel_manager) {
123 RTC_DCHECK(media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO ||
124 media_type == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO);
125 RTC_DCHECK(channel_manager_);
126}
127
128RtpTransceiver::RtpTransceiver(
129 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderProxyWithInternal<RtpSenderInternal>> sender,
130 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpReceiverProxyWithInternal<RtpReceiverInternal>>
131 receiver,
132 cricket::ChannelManager* channel_manager,
133 std::vector<RtpHeaderExtensionCapability> header_extensions_offered,
134 std::function<void()> on_negotiation_needed)
135 : thread_(GetCurrentTaskQueueOrThread()),
136 unified_plan_(true),
137 media_type_(sender->media_type()),
138 channel_manager_(channel_manager),
139 header_extensions_to_offer_(std::move(header_extensions_offered)),
140 on_negotiation_needed_(std::move(on_negotiation_needed)) {
141 RTC_DCHECK(media_type_ == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO ||
142 media_type_ == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO);
143 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(sender->media_type(), receiver->media_type());
144 RTC_DCHECK(channel_manager_);
145 senders_.push_back(sender);
146 receivers_.push_back(receiver);
147}

149RtpTransceiver::~RtpTransceiver() {
150 // TODO(tommi): On Android, when running PeerConnectionClientTest (e.g.
151 // PeerConnectionClientTest#testCameraSwitch), the instance doesn't get
152 // deleted on `thread_`. See if we can fix that.
153 if (!stopped_) {
154 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
155 StopInternal();
156 }
157}

159void RtpTransceiver::SetChannel(cricket::ChannelInterface* channel) {
160 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
161 // Cannot set a non-null channel on a stopped transceiver.
162 if (stopped_ && channel) {
163 return;
164 }
165
166 RTC_DCHECK(channel || channel_);
167
168 RTC_LOG_THREAD_BLOCK_COUNT();
169
170 if (channel_) {
171 signaling_thread_safety_->SetNotAlive();
172 signaling_thread_safety_ = nullptr;
173 }
174
175 if (channel) {
176 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(media_type(), channel->media_type());
177 signaling_thread_safety_ = PendingTaskSafetyFlag::Create();
178 }
179
180 // An alternative to this, could be to require SetChannel to be called
181 // on the network thread. The channel object operates for the most part
182 // on the network thread, as part of its initialization being on the network
183 // thread is required, so setting a channel object as part of the construction
184 // (without thread hopping) might be the more efficient thing to do than
185 // how SetChannel works today.
186 // Similarly, if the channel() accessor is limited to the network thread, that
187 // helps with keeping the channel implementation requirements being met and
188 // avoids synchronization for accessing the pointer or network related state.
189 channel_manager_->network_thread()->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&]() {
190 if (channel_) {
191 channel_->SetFirstPacketReceivedCallback(nullptr);
192 }
193
194 channel_ = channel;
195
196 if (channel_) {
197 channel_->SetFirstPacketReceivedCallback(
198 [thread = thread_, flag = signaling_thread_safety_, this]() mutable {
199 thread->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
200 std::move(flag), [this]() { OnFirstPacketReceived(); }));
201 });
202 }
203 });
204
205 for (const auto& sender : senders_) {
206 sender->internal()->SetMediaChannel(channel_ ? channel_->media_channel()
207 : nullptr);
208 }
209
210 RTC_DCHECK_BLOCK_COUNT_NO_MORE_THAN(1);
211
212 for (const auto& receiver : receivers_) {
213 if (!channel_) {
214 receiver->internal()->Stop();
215 } else {
216 receiver->internal()->SetMediaChannel(channel_->media_channel());
217 }
218 }
219}

221void RtpTransceiver::AddSender(
222 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpSenderProxyWithInternal<RtpSenderInternal>> sender) {
223 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
224 RTC_DCHECK(!stopped_);
225 RTC_DCHECK(!unified_plan_);
226 RTC_DCHECK(sender);
227 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(media_type(), sender->media_type());
228 RTC_DCHECK(!absl::c_linear_search(senders_, sender));
229 senders_.push_back(sender);
230}
231
232bool RtpTransceiver::RemoveSender(RtpSenderInterface* sender) {
233 RTC_DCHECK(!unified_plan_);
234 if (sender) {
235 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(media_type(), sender->media_type());
236 }
237 auto it = absl::c_find(senders_, sender);
238 if (it == senders_.end()) {
239 return false;
240 }
241 (*it)->internal()->Stop();
242 senders_.erase(it);
243 return true;
244}
245
246void RtpTransceiver::AddReceiver(
247 rtc::scoped_refptr<RtpReceiverProxyWithInternal<RtpReceiverInternal>>
248 receiver) {
249 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
250 RTC_DCHECK(!stopped_);
251 RTC_DCHECK(!unified_plan_);
252 RTC_DCHECK(receiver);
253 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(media_type(), receiver->media_type());
254 RTC_DCHECK(!absl::c_linear_search(receivers_, receiver));
255 receivers_.push_back(receiver);
256}
257
258bool RtpTransceiver::RemoveReceiver(RtpReceiverInterface* receiver) {
259 RTC_DCHECK(!unified_plan_);
260 if (receiver) {
261 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(media_type(), receiver->media_type());
262 }
263 auto it = absl::c_find(receivers_, receiver);
264 if (it == receivers_.end()) {
265 return false;
266 }
267 // `Stop()` will clear the internally cached pointer to the media channel.
268 (*it)->internal()->Stop();
269 receivers_.erase(it);
270 return true;
271}

312void RtpTransceiver::set_current_direction(RtpTransceiverDirection direction) {
313 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Changing transceiver (MID=" << mid_.value_or("<not set>")
314 << ") current direction from "
315 << (current_direction_ ? RtpTransceiverDirectionToString(
316 *current_direction_)
317 : "<not set>")
318 << " to " << RtpTransceiverDirectionToString(direction)
319 << ".";
320 current_direction_ = direction;
321 if (RtpTransceiverDirectionHasSend(*current_direction_)) {
322 has_ever_been_used_to_send_ = true;
323 }
324}

340RtpTransceiverDirection RtpTransceiver::direction() const {
341 if (unified_plan_ && stopping())
342 return webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirection::kStopped;
343
344 return direction_;
345}
346
347RTCError RtpTransceiver::SetDirectionWithError(
348 RtpTransceiverDirection new_direction) {
349 if (unified_plan_ && stopping()) {
350 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
351 "Cannot set direction on a stopping transceiver.");
352 }
353 if (new_direction == direction_)
354 return RTCError::OK();
355
356 if (new_direction == RtpTransceiverDirection::kStopped) {
357 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
358 "The set direction 'stopped' is invalid.");
359 }
360
361 direction_ = new_direction;
362 on_negotiation_needed_();
363
364 return RTCError::OK();
365}

372 return current_direction_;

380void RtpTransceiver::StopSendingAndReceiving() {
381 // 1. Let sender be transceiver.[[Sender]].
382 // 2. Let receiver be transceiver.[[Receiver]].
383 //
384 // 3. Stop sending media with sender.
385 //
386 // 4. Send an RTCP BYE for each RTP stream that was being sent by sender, as
387 // specified in [RFC3550].
388 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
389 for (const auto& sender : senders_)
390 sender->internal()->Stop();
391
392 // 5. Stop receiving media with receiver.
393 for (const auto& receiver : receivers_)
394 receiver->internal()->StopAndEndTrack();
395
396 stopping_ = true;
397 direction_ = webrtc::RtpTransceiverDirection::kInactive;
398}
399
400RTCError RtpTransceiver::StopStandard() {
401 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
402 // If we're on Plan B, do what Stop() used to do there.
403 if (!unified_plan_) {
404 StopInternal();
405 return RTCError::OK();
406 }
407 // 1. Let transceiver be the RTCRtpTransceiver object on which the method is
408 // invoked.
409 //
410 // 2. Let connection be the RTCPeerConnection object associated with
411 // transceiver.
412 //
413 // 3. If connection.[[IsClosed]] is true, throw an InvalidStateError.
414 if (is_pc_closed_) {
415 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(RTCErrorType::INVALID_STATE,
416 "PeerConnection is closed.");
417 }
418
419 // 4. If transceiver.[[Stopping]] is true, abort these steps.
420 if (stopping_)
421 return RTCError::OK();
422
423 // 5. Stop sending and receiving given transceiver, and update the
424 // negotiation-needed flag for connection.
425 StopSendingAndReceiving();
426 on_negotiation_needed_();
427
428 return RTCError::OK();
429}
430
431void RtpTransceiver::StopInternal() {
432 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
433 StopTransceiverProcedure();
434}
435
436void RtpTransceiver::StopTransceiverProcedure() {
437 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
438 // As specified in the "Stop the RTCRtpTransceiver" procedure
439 // 1. If transceiver.[[Stopping]] is false, stop sending and receiving given
440 // transceiver.
441 if (!stopping_)
442 StopSendingAndReceiving();
443
444 // 2. Set transceiver.[[Stopped]] to true.
445 stopped_ = true;
446
447 // Signal the updated change to the senders.
448 for (const auto& sender : senders_)
449 sender->internal()->SetTransceiverAsStopped();
450
451 // 3. Set transceiver.[[Receptive]] to false.
452 // 4. Set transceiver.[[CurrentDirection]] to null.
453 current_direction_ = absl::nullopt;
454}
455
456RTCError RtpTransceiver::SetCodecPreferences(
457 rtc::ArrayView<RtpCodecCapability> codec_capabilities) {
458 RTC_DCHECK(unified_plan_);
459
460 // 3. If codecs is an empty list, set transceiver's [[PreferredCodecs]] slot
461 // to codecs and abort these steps.
462 if (codec_capabilities.empty()) {
463 codec_preferences_.clear();
464 return RTCError::OK();
465 }
466
467 // 4. Remove any duplicate values in codecs.
468 std::vector<RtpCodecCapability> codecs;
469 absl::c_remove_copy_if(codec_capabilities, std::back_inserter(codecs),
470 [&codecs](const RtpCodecCapability& codec) {
471 return absl::c_linear_search(codecs, codec);
472 });
473
474 // 6. to 8.
475 RTCError result;
476 if (media_type_ == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
477 std::vector<cricket::AudioCodec> recv_codecs, send_codecs;
478 channel_manager_->GetSupportedAudioReceiveCodecs(&recv_codecs);
479 channel_manager_->GetSupportedAudioSendCodecs(&send_codecs);
480
481 result = VerifyCodecPreferences(codecs, send_codecs, recv_codecs);
482 } else if (media_type_ == cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
483 std::vector<cricket::VideoCodec> recv_codecs, send_codecs;
484 channel_manager_->GetSupportedVideoReceiveCodecs(&recv_codecs);
485 channel_manager_->GetSupportedVideoSendCodecs(&send_codecs);
486
487 result = VerifyCodecPreferences(codecs, send_codecs, recv_codecs);
488 }
489
490 if (result.ok()) {
491 codec_preferences_ = codecs;
492 }
493
494 return result;
495}

497std::vector<RtpHeaderExtensionCapability>
498RtpTransceiver::HeaderExtensionsToOffer() const {
499 return header_extensions_to_offer_;
500}

502std::vector<RtpHeaderExtensionCapability>
503RtpTransceiver::HeaderExtensionsNegotiated() const {
504 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
505 std::vector<RtpHeaderExtensionCapability> result;
506 for (const auto& ext : negotiated_header_extensions_) {
507 result.emplace_back(ext.uri, ext.id, RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendRecv);
508 }
509 return result;
510}
511
512RTCError RtpTransceiver::SetOfferedRtpHeaderExtensions(
513 rtc::ArrayView<const RtpHeaderExtensionCapability>
514 header_extensions_to_offer) {
515 for (const auto& entry : header_extensions_to_offer) {
516 // Handle unsupported requests for mandatory extensions as per
517 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-extensions/#rtcrtptransceiver-interface.
518 // Note:
519 // - We do not handle setOfferedRtpHeaderExtensions algorithm step 2.1,
520 // this has to be checked on a higher level. We naturally error out
521 // in the handling of Step 2.2 if an unset URI is encountered.
522
523 // Step 2.2.
524 // Handle unknown extensions.
525 auto it = std::find_if(
526 header_extensions_to_offer_.begin(), header_extensions_to_offer_.end(),
527 [&entry](const auto& offered) { return entry.uri == offered.uri; });
528 if (it == header_extensions_to_offer_.end()) {
529 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::UNSUPPORTED_PARAMETER,
530 "Attempted to modify an unoffered extension.");
531 }
532
533 // Step 2.4-2.5.
534 // - Use of the transceiver interface indicates unified plan is in effect,
535 // hence the MID extension needs to be enabled.
536 // - Also handle the mandatory video orientation extensions.
537 if ((entry.uri == RtpExtension::kMidUri ||
538 entry.uri == RtpExtension::kVideoRotationUri) &&
539 entry.direction != RtpTransceiverDirection::kSendRecv) {
540 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_MODIFICATION,
541 "Attempted to stop a mandatory extension.");
542 }
543 }
544
545 // Apply mutation after error checking.
546 for (const auto& entry : header_extensions_to_offer) {
547 auto it = std::find_if(
548 header_extensions_to_offer_.begin(), header_extensions_to_offer_.end(),
549 [&entry](const auto& offered) { return entry.uri == offered.uri; });
550 it->direction = entry.direction;
551 }
552
553 return RTCError::OK();
554}

556void RtpTransceiver::OnNegotiationUpdate(
557 SdpType sdp_type,
558 const cricket::MediaContentDescription* content) {
559 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
560 RTC_DCHECK(content);
561 if (sdp_type == SdpType::kAnswer)
562 negotiated_header_extensions_ = content->rtp_header_extensions();
563}

566 is_pc_closed_ = true;
